(256, '<p>The word gambut (peat) is taken from the name of a village, Desa Gambut (now Gambut sub-district), which is located about 10 km east of Banjarmasin, South Kalimantan. It is at this place that for the first time, rice has been successfully cultivated in peat soiled rice fields. In the soil taxonomy system, peat soils are grouped into a separate soil order called histosols, which means that the land is predominantly composed of organic soil materials in the form of the remains of plant tissues, the nature and the characteristics of peat soils can be determined based on physical and chemical properties.</p><p>Gambut has dark brown to blackish colors. Although its basic materials are gray, brown, or reddish, after decomposition, the dark humic compounds will appear. Furthermore, based on the weight on the contents, peat soil or gambut, which has undergone further decomposition, has a content weight ranging from 0.2 to 0.3 g/cm3. Due to the low content weight, peat has a <strong>large capacity as water storage</strong>, about 2-4 times its dry weight. In fact, moss peat that has not been decomposed can store up to 12 or 15 even 20 times more water than its own weight. In addition, peat soil has a large absorption area, which is up to 4 times greater than montmorillonite clay. Next, peat soil has acidic reaction properties. Decomposition of organic matters will produce organic acids that accumulate in the body of soil hence increasing the acidity of the ideal peat soil. Generally, peat soil shows real resistance to changes in pH when compared to mineral soils. As a result, peat soil requires more limestone to increase the pH at the same level of the value of mineral soil. Thus, peat soil requires a higher dose of fertilizers than mineral soil.</p><p>Furthermore, based on the nutrients contained in it, peat soil is a type of nutrient-poor soil. High levels of N and organic matter in peat soils are also accompanied by a high N nitrification process so that the activity of heterotrophic organisms is not well stimulated and the organisms active in the nitrification process can carry out their activities. Therefore, the levels of P (phosphorus) and K (potassium) of peat soil are very responsive to the fertilization using P and K.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The phrase ‘large capacity as water storage’ in paragraph 2 can be replaced by…</p>', NULL, 'pilihan_ganda', '<p>Tipe soal di atas adalah <i>word substitution</i> yang bertujuan untuk mencari pengganti frasa <i>large capacity as water storage</i> di paragraf 2.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Frasa yang ditanyakan pada soal ada pada kalimat ke-4 paragraf 2. Kalimatnya adalah <i>‘Due to the low content weight, peat has a large capacity as water storage, about 2-4 times its dry weight’ (karena kandungan yang rendah, gambut memiliki kapasitas yang besar sebagai penyimpan air, sekitar 2-4 kali berat saat ia kering). Frasa ‘large capacity as water storage’ memiliki makna kapasitas yang besar sebagai penyimpan air.</i></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Opsi A (kekuatan untuk menahan arus air yang deras) tidak tepat karena frasa pada soal tidak membahas tentang kemampuan untuk menahan arus air.</p><p>Opsi B (kapasitas untuk menjaga stabilitas arus air) tidak tepat karena frasa pada soal tidak membahas tentang stabilitas arus air.</p><p>Opsi C (kualitas dan kuantitas air yang tinggi) tidak tepat karena frasa pada soal tidak membahas tentang kualitas dan kuantitas air yang tinggi.</p><p>Opsi D (berpotensi untuk membuat penyimpanan air yang besar) tidak tepat karena frasa pada soal tidak membahas tentang potensi tanah untuk membuat penyimpanan air yang besar.</p><p>Opsi E (kemampuan untuk menyimpan sejumlah besar air) tepat karena frasa membahas tentang kemampuan tanah untuk menyimpan air yang banyak.</p><p><strong>Jadi, jawaban yang tepat adalah E.</strong></p>', NULL, 'Vocabulary in Context', '2025-06-22 05:44:43', '2025-06-22 05:44:43', NULL, 7, 26, 7, 'Diterima'),
(257, '<p>The word gambut (peat) is taken from the name of a village, Desa Gambut (now Gambut sub-district), which is located about 10 km east of Banjarmasin, South Kalimantan. It is at this place that for the first time, rice has been successfully cultivated in peat soiled rice fields. In the soil taxonomy system, peat soils are grouped into a separate soil order called histosols, which means that the land is predominantly composed of organic soil materials in the form of the remains of plant tissues, the nature and the characteristics of peat soils can be determined based on physical and chemical properties.</p><p>Gambut has dark brown to blackish colors. Although its basic materials are gray, brown, or reddish, after decomposition, the dark humic compounds will appear. Furthermore, based on the weight on the contents, peat soil or gambut, which has undergone further decomposition, has a content weight ranging from 0.2 to 0.3 g/cm3. Due to the low content weight, peat has a large capacity as water storage, about 2-4 times its dry weight. In fact, moss peat that has not been decomposed can store up to 12 or 15 even 20 times more water than its own weight. In addition, peat soil has a large absorption area, which is up to 4 times greater than montmorillonite clay. Next, peat soil has acidic reaction properties. Decomposition of organic matters will produce organic acids that accumulate in the body of soil hence increasing the acidity of the ideal peat soil. Generally, peat soil shows real resistance to changes in pH when compared to mineral soils. As a result, peat soil requires more limestone to increase the pH at the same level of the value of mineral soil. Thus, peat soil requires a higher dose of fertilizers than mineral soil.</p><p>Furthermore, based on the nutrients contained in it, peat soil is a type of nutrient-poor soil. High levels of N and organic matter in peat soils are also accompanied by a high N nitrification process so that the activity of heterotrophic organisms is not well stimulated and the organisms active in the nitrification process can carry out their activities. Therefore, the levels of P (phosphorus) and K (potassium) of peat soil are very responsive to the fertilization using P and K.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>What is the main idea of the passage?</p>', NULL, 'pilihan_ganda', '<p>Tipe soal di atas adalah <i>Main Idea and Topic</i> yang bertujuan untuk mencari ide utama pada teks di atas.</p><p>Secara umum, teks di atas membahas tentang karakteristik tanah gambut. Tanah gambut memiliki karakteristik berwarna hitam dan memiliki kemampuan untuk menahan air. Meskipun tanah gambut memiliki unsur hara yang sedikit, di Kalimantan tepatnya di desa Gambut, tanah gambut dapat dijadikan lahan untuk menanam padi.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Opsi A (tanah gambut memiliki sifat yang baik sebagai pupuk) tidak tepat. Kalimat pada opsi ini bertentangan dengan pernyataan <i>‘peat soil is a type of nutrient-poor soil’</i> yang berarti tanah gambut merupakan jenis tanah yang kurang zat hara sehingga, tanah ini membutuhkan pupuk.</p><p>Opsi B (tanah gambut berbeda secara fisik dan kimia) tidak tepat. Teks di atas tidak membandingkan perbedaan tanah gambut secara fisik dan kimia.</p><p>Opsi C (tanah gambut memiliki beberapa sifat fisik dan kimia tertentu) tepat. Teks di atas menjelaskan tentang karakteristik fisik dan kimia dari tanah gambut.</p><p>Opsi D (tanah gambut memiliki sifat kimia yang sedikit berbeda dari tanah liat) tidak tepat. Teks tidak membahas perbedaan tanah gambut dan tanah liat.</p><p>Opsi E (tanah gambut berwarna coklat karena sifat fisik dan kimianya) tidak tepat. Teks tidak hanya membahas warna tanah gambut.</p><p><strong>Jadi, jawaban yang tepat adalah C.</strong></p>', NULL, 'Main Idea and Topic', '2025-06-22 05:46:37', '2025-06-22 05:46:37', NULL, 7, 26, 7, 'Diterima'),
(258, '<p>The word gambut (peat) is taken from the name of a village, Desa Gambut (now Gambut sub-district), which is located about 10 km east of Banjarmasin, South Kalimantan. It is at this place that for the first time, rice has been successfully cultivated in peat soiled rice fields. In the soil taxonomy system, peat soils are grouped into a separate soil order called histosols, which means that the land is predominantly composed of organic soil materials in the form of the remains of plant tissues, the nature and the characteristics of peat soils can be determined based on physical and chemical properties.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Gambut has dark brown to blackish colors. Although its basic materials are gray, brown, or reddish, after decomposition, the dark humic compounds will appear. Furthermore, based on the weight on the contents, peat soil or gambut, which has undergone further decomposition, has a content weight ranging from 0.2 to 0.3 g/cm3. Due to the low content weight, peat has a large capacity as water storage, about 2-4 times its dry weight. In fact, moss peat that has not been decomposed can store up to 12 or 15 even 20 times more water than its own weight. In addition, peat soil has a large absorption area, which is up to 4 times greater than montmorillonite clay. Next, peat soil has acidic reaction properties. Decomposition of organic matters will produce organic acids that accumulate in the body of soil hence increasing the acidity of the ideal peat soil. Generally, peat soil shows real resistance to changes in pH when compared to mineral soils. As a result, peat soil requires more limestone to increase the pH at the same level of the value of mineral soil. Thus, peat soil requires a higher dose of fertilizers than mineral soil.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Furthermore, based on the nutrients contained in it, peat soil is a type of nutrient-poor soil. High levels of N and organic matter in peat soils are also accompanied by a high N nitrification process so that the activity of heterotrophic organisms is not well stimulated and the organisms active in the nitrification process can carry out their activities. Therefore, the levels of P (phosphorus) and K (potassium) of peat soil are very responsive to the fertilization using P and K.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The purpose of the writer in writing the sentence <i>‘Therefore, the levels of P (phosphorus) and K (potassium) of peat soils are generally lower than that of the mineral soils. Also, the plants cultivated on the peat soil are very responsive to the fertilization using P and K’</i> in paragraph 4 is to…</p>', NULL, 'pilihan_ganda', '<p>Tipe soal di atas adalah <i>Author’s Writing Organization</i> yang bertujuan untuk menemukan tujuan penulis dalam menuliskan sebuah kalimat <i>‘Therefore, the levels of P (phosphorus) and K (potassium) of peat soils are generally lower than that of the mineral soils. Also, the plants cultivated on the peat soil are very responsive to the fertilization using P and K’</i></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Kalimat yang ditanyakan pada soal ada pada paragraf ke empat kalimat terakhir. Kalimat tersebut memiliki makna ‘Oleh karena itu, umumnya kadar P (fosfor) dan K (kalium) tanah gambut lebih rendah dibandingkan dengan tanah mineral. Selain itu, tanaman yang dibudidayakan di lahan gambut sangat responsif terhadap pemupukan menggunakan P dan K’.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Opsi A (mengidentifikasi tanah mineral yang akan diberi pupuk P dan K) tidak tepat. Pada kalimat tidak dijelaskan cara mengidentifikasi tanah mineral yang akan diberikan pupuk P dan K.</p><p>Opsi B (mendukung peningkatan produksi pupuk P dan K) tidak tepat. Pada kalimat tidak dijelaskan bahwa produksi pupuk P dan K akan meningkat karena budidaya di lahan gambut.</p><p>Opsi C (mengkonfirmasi bahwa pupuk terbaik untuk tanah gambut adalah P dan K) tepat. Pada kalimat tersebut, penulis memberi informasi bahwa tanah gambut sangat responsif terhadap pupuk P dan K. Sehingga, tanah gambut membutuhkan pupuk P dan K.</p><p>Opsi D (memberikan contoh cara pemberian pupuk P dan K pada tanah gambut) tidak tepat. Penulis tidak memaparkan bagaimana cara memberikan pupuk P dan K pada lahan gambut.</p><p>Opsi E (menjelaskan bahwa pupuk P dan K hanya diproduksi untuk tanah gambut) tidak tepat. Pada kalimat, penulis juga memaparkan bahwa pupuk P dan K dapat digunakan pada tanah mineral.</p><p><strong>Jadi, jawaban yang tepat adalah C.</strong></p>', NULL, 'Author\'s Attitude and Writing Organization', '2025-06-22 05:49:28', '2025-06-22 05:49:28', NULL, 7, 26, 7, 'Diterima'),
(259, '<p>The word gambut (peat) is taken from the name of a village, Desa Gambut (now Gambut sub-district), which is located about 10 km east of Banjarmasin, South Kalimantan. It is at this place that for the first time, rice has been successfully cultivated in peat soiled rice fields. In the soil taxonomy system, peat soils are grouped into a separate soil order called histosols, which means that the land is predominantly composed of organic soil materials in the form of the remains of plant tissues, the nature and the characteristics of peat soils can be determined based on physical and chemical properties.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Gambut has dark brown to blackish colors. Although its basic materials are gray, brown, or reddish, after decomposition, the dark humic compounds will appear. Furthermore, based on the weight on the contents, peat soil or gambut, which has undergone further decomposition, has a content weight ranging from 0.2 to 0.3 g/cm3. Due to the low content weight, peat has a <strong>large capacity as water storage</strong>, about 2-4 times its dry weight. In fact, moss peat that has not been decomposed can store up to 12 or 15 even 20 times more water than its own weight. In addition, peat soil has a large absorption area, which is up to 4 times greater than montmorillonite clay. Next, peat soil has acidic reaction properties. Decomposition of organic matters will produce organic acids that accumulate in the body of soil hence increasing the acidity of the ideal peat soil. Generally, peat soil shows real resistance to changes in pH when compared to mineral soils. As a result, peat soil requires more limestone to increase the pH at the same level of the value of mineral soil. Thus, peat soil requires a higher dose of fertilizers than mineral soil.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Furthermore, based on the nutrients contained in it, peat soil is a type of nutrient-poor soil. High levels of N and organic matter in peat soils are also accompanied by a high N nitrification process so that the activity of heterotrophic organisms is not well stimulated and the organisms active in the nitrification process can carry out their activities. Therefore, the levels of P (phosphorus) and K (potassium) of peat soil are very responsive to the fertilization using P and K.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>What most likely motivates the writer to write the passage?</p>', NULL, 'pilihan_ganda', '<p>Tipe soal di atas adalah <i>Author’s Purpose</i> yang bertujuan untuk mengidentifikasi tujuan penulis dalam menuliskan teks di atas.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Secara umum, teks di atas membahas tentang karakteristik tanah gambut. Tanah gambut memiliki karakteristik berwarna hitam dan memiliki kemampuan untuk menahan air. Meskipun tanah gambut memiliki unsur hara yang sedikit, di kalimantan tepatnya di desa Gambut, tanah gambut dapat dijadikan lahan untuk menanam padi.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Opsi A (Menanam tanaman di lahan gambut dinilai tidak efektif memberikan hasil yang maksimal) tidak tepat. Penulis menulis bahwa tanah gambut memiliki kandungan zat hara yang sedikit namun bukan berarti tidak dapat memberikan hasil panen yang maksimal karena tanah gambut dapat diberi pupuk P dan K.</p><p>Opsi B (orang-orang pikir tanah gambut hanya dapat ditemukan pinggir sungai atau laut) tidak tepat. Penulis tidak menyampaikan asumsi orang-orang terhadap tanah gambut.</p><p>Opsi C (pengetahuan masyarakat tentang menanam tanaman di tanah gambut masih terbatas) tidak tepat. Penulis tidak menjelaskan pengetahuan masyarakat umum terhadap tanah gambut.</p><p>Opsi D (masyarakat membutuhkan informasi tentang tanah gambut sebagai lahan pertanian) tepat. Penulis menjelaskan bagaimana tanah gambut dapat dimanfaatkan sebagai lahan pertanian meskipun mengandung zat hara yang sedikit.</p><p>Opsi E (tidak banyak orang tau keasaman tanah gambut di alam) tidak tepat. Penulis hanya menjelaskan sedikit tentang tingkat keasaman pada tanah gambut.</p><p><strong>Jadi, jawaban yang tepat adalah D.</strong></p>', NULL, 'Purpose of the Text', '2025-06-22 05:52:50', '2025-06-22 05:52:50', NULL, 7, 26, 7, 'Diterima'),
(260, '<p>The use of modern chemical drugs and herbal medicines, including herbs, simultaneously to treat certain diseases must be exercised carefully. Random combined use can lead to health worsening. Clinical trials showed the use of simvastatin as anti-cholesterol drugs or a mixture of guava leaves, Javanese turmeric (temulawak) roots, and Dutch teak leaves as traditional medicine gave good results if they are used separately. But, if combined, the results are harmful. Similar harms happen in the combined use of metformin and black tea to treat diabetes. If both are used individually, they can reduce blood sugar levels in large quantities. However, if combined, the decrease in blood sugar content is actually very small.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>As for herbal medicines, besides being absorbed more slowly by the body, sometimes they are binding substances from chemical drugs. As a result, the effect of chemical drugs is not optimal. Ginseng should not be combined with heart drugs because it will worsen the heart condition. In addition, garlic, which is also an anticoagulant herbal medicine, should not be combined with chemical drugs such as acetasol or clopidropil because it will cause bleeding.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Indonesians know and realize the benefits of medicinal plants for a long time. However, the traditional Indonesian medicine industry has not developed. Currently there are 6 phytopharmacologically based medicines and 31 standardized herbal medicines. The herbs in Indonesia are thousands in number. Jamu is the lowest level in the grouping of the Indonesian traditional medicines, followed by standardized herbal medicines and phytopharmacologically based medicines as the highest level. To improve the status of herbal medicines to standardized herbal medicines, there must be a non-clinical test. To be phytopharmacologically based medicines, clinical trials and non-clinical trials must be carried out on these medicines. Because of this, many herbal producers are reluctant to improve the status of their products because even without such complicated procedures, the herbal has already sold well. Manufacturers will only increase the status of their products to standardized herbal medicines or phytopharmacologically based medicines to ensure the safety of their products to consumers and export interests.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The writer emphasizes the importance of separating the consumption of chemical medicines from that of the herbal medicines in paragraph(s) ....</p>', NULL, 'pilihan_ganda', '<p>Tipe soal di atas adalah <i>Finding Detailed Information</i> yang bertujuan untuk mencari informasi tentang pentingnya membedakan konsumsi obat kimia dan obat herbal.</p><p>Paragraf pertama, membahas tentang keuntungan menggunakan obat herbal dan obat-obatan kimia modern jika dipakai secara terpisah namun, akan berdampak buruk jika dipakai secara bersamaan. Paragraf kedua membahas tentang bagaimana obat herbal dapat memperburuk pengobatan jika dipakai secara bersamaan dengan obat-obatan kimia. Paragraf ketiga membahas tentang obat-obatan tradisional yang dipakai di Indonesia.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Oleh karena itu, paragraf yang menjelaskan tentang pentingnya membedakan konsumsi obat kimia dan obat herbal ada pada paragraf satu dan dua.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Opsi A tidak tepat karena paragraf yang membahas pentingnya membedakan konsumsi obat kimia dan obat herbal ada di paragraf 1 dan 2.</p><p>Opsi B tidak tepat karena paragraf yang membahas pentingnya membedakan konsumsi obat kimia dan obat herbal ada di paragraf 1 dan 2.</p><p>Opsi C tidak tepat karena paragraf 3 membahas tentang obat-obatan herbal yang dipakai di Indonesia.</p><p>Opsi D tepat karena paragraf yang membahas pentingnya membedakan konsumsi obat kimia dan obat herbal ada di paragraf 1 dan 2.</p><p>Opsi E tidak tepat karena paragraf 3 membahas tentang obat-obatan herbal yang dipakai di Indonesia.</p><p><strong>Jadi, jawaban yang tepat adalah D.</strong></p>', NULL, 'Finding Detailed Information', '2025-06-22 05:54:15', '2025-06-22 05:54:15', NULL, 7, 26, 7, 'Diterima');
