(337, '<p>(1)As we sail through the 21st century, technology in the classroom is becoming more and more predominant. Tablets are replacing our textbooks, and we can research just about anything that we want to on our smartphones. Social media has become commonplace, and the way we use technology has completely transformed the way we live or lives.</p><p>(2)Educators, too, have seen firsthand the benefits of technology in the classroom. According to a study by IT Trade Association CompTIA just released this month, around 75 percent of educators think that technology has a positive impact on the education process. Educators also recognize the importance of developing these technological skills in students so they will be prepared to enter the workforce once they complete their schooling.</p><p>(3)The impact that technology has had on today’s schools has been quite significant. This widespread adoption of technology has completely changed how teachers teach and students learn. Teachers are learning how to teach with emerging technologies (tablets, iPads, Smart Boards, digital cameras, and computers), while students are using advanced technology to shape how they learn. By embracing and integrating technology in the classroom, we are setting our students up for a successful life outside of school.</p><p>(4)A few benefits of using technology are obvious. Technology in the classroom makes learning more fun. Technology not only prepares students for the future, but also improves retention rate. Besides, technology helps students learn at their own pace, and technology connects learning sources with students.</p><p>(5)As technology changes very fast, educators need to keep up with the times in order to best prepare our students for this ever-changing world that we live in. While we just saw how integrating technology into the classroom has its benefits, it is important to note that traditional learning processes are just as essential. Take time to learn about each element of ed-tech that you will incorporate into your classroom.</p><p><i>(Adapted from: http://www.teachhub.com/benefits-technology-classroom)</i></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>What does the passage mainly deal with?</p>', NULL, 'pilihan_ganda', '<p>Tipe soal ini merupakan <i>Main Idea and Topic</i> yang bertujuan untuk mencari topik yang dibahas pada teks tersebut secara keseluruhan.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Teks tersebut membahas pesatnya teknologi yang digunakan dalam pendidikan saat ini. Kalimat pertama pada paragraf 1, “<i>..., technology in the classroom is becoming more and more predominant</i>” (Teknologi di dalam ruang kelas saat ini menjadi lebih dominant), menunjukkan kondisi bagaimana teknologi sekarang mulai masuk ke dalam ruang kelas dan terintegrasi dengan kegiatan pembelajaran.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Kemudian kalimat kedua paragraf 4, “<i>Besides, technology helps students learn at their own pace, and technology connects learning sources with students.</i>\" (Selain itu, teknologi membantu siswa belajar dengan kecepatan mereka sendiri, dan teknologi menghubungkan sumber belajar dengan siswa), menunjukkan bagaimana pembelajaran menggunakan teknologi tersebut memiliki dampak positif bagi para siswa.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Opsi A (Mengembangkan kemampuan teknologi para siswa) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Pada teks tersebut, pembahasan tidak berfokus terhadap pengembangan kemampuan teknologi untuk para siswa.</p><p>Opsi B (Mempersiapkan para pendidik dengan sosial media yang berguna) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Teks tersebut membahas para pendidik yang harus fokus pada pengembangan teknologi untuk diterapkan di dalam kelas, bukan sosial media semata.</p><p>Opsi C (Meningkatkan pengetahuan para siswa melalui teknologi) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Pada teks tersebut tidak dijelaskan poin-poin penting untuk meningkatkan pengetahuan siswa melalui teknologi.</p><p>Opsi D (Mengintegrasikan teknologi ke dalam proses pendidikan) <strong>tepat</strong>. Pernyataan pada opsi ini merupakan topik yang dikembangkan penulis di dalam teks berdasarkan konteks pembahasan di atas.</p><p>Opsi E (Menggunakan keunggulan teknologi untuk terhubung dengan siswa) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Di dalam teks tidak ada petunjuk bagaimana teknologi dapat membantu pengajar untuk terhubung dengan siswa.</p><p><strong>Jadi, jawaban yang tepat adalah D.</strong></p>', NULL, 'Main Idea and Topic', '2025-06-30 03:33:08', '2025-06-30 03:33:08', NULL, 7, 35, 7, 'Diterima'),
(338, '<p>(1)As we sail through the 21st century, technology in the classroom is becoming more and more predominant. Tablets are replacing our textbooks, and we can research just about anything that we want to on our smartphones. Social media has become commonplace, and the way we use technology has completely <strong>transformed</strong> the way we live or lives.</p><p>(2)Educators, too, have seen firsthand the benefits of technology in the classroom. According to a study by IT Trade Association CompTIA just released this month, around 75 percent of educators think that technology has a positive impact on the education process. Educators also recognize the importance of developing these technological skills in students so they will be prepared to enter the workforce once they complete their schooling.</p><p>(3)The impact that technology has had on today’s schools has been quite significant. This widespread adoption of technology has completely changed how teachers teach and students learn. Teachers are learning how to teach with emerging technologies (tablets, iPads, Smart Boards, digital cameras, and computers), while students are using advanced technology to shape how they learn. By embracing and integrating technology in the classroom, we are setting our students up for a successful life outside of school.</p><p>(4)A few benefits of using technology are obvious. Technology in the classroom makes learning more fun. Technology not only prepares students for the future, but also improves retention rate. Besides, technology helps students learn at their own pace, and technology connects learning sources with students.</p><p>(5)As technology changes very fast, educators need to keep up with the times in order to best prepare our students for this ever-changing world that we live in. While we just saw how integrating technology into the classroom has its benefits, it is important to note that traditional learning processes are just as essential. Take time to learn about each element of ed-tech that you will incorporate into your classroom.</p><p><i>(Adapted from: http://www.teachhub.com/benefits-technology-classroom)</i></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Based on the passage, the word <i>transformed</i> in paragraph 1 means…</p>', NULL, 'pilihan_ganda', '<p>Tipe soal ini adalah <i>synonym</i> yang bertujuan untuk mencari tahu persamaan kata yang sesuai dengan kata yang bertanda tebal.</p><p>Kata <i>transformed</i> tertera pada kalimat terakhir paragraf 1; “<i>Social media has become commonplace, and the way we use technology has completely <strong>transformed</strong> the way we live or lives</i>” (Media sosial telah menjadi hal yang umum, dan cara kita menggunakan teknologi telah sepenuhnya <strong>mengubah</strong> cara kita hidup).</p><p>Kata <i>transform</i> memiliki arti <strong>mengubah</strong> yang sesuai dengan kata <i>changed</i> (mengubah) pada opsi C.</p><p>Opsi A (Terawat), Opsi B (Berinovasi), Opsi D (Meningkatkan), Opsi E (Memperkuat) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Keempat opsi tersebut tidak memiliki kesesuaian makna dengan kata <i>transform</i> pada kalimat di dalam teks.</p><p><strong>Jadi, jawaban yang tepat adalah C.</strong></p>', NULL, 'Synonym', '2025-06-30 03:34:05', '2025-06-30 03:34:05', NULL, 7, 35, 7, 'Diterima'),
(339, '<p>(1)As we sail through the 21st century, technology in the classroom is becoming more and more predominant. Tablets are replacing our textbooks, and we can research just about anything that we want to on our smartphones. Social media has become commonplace, and the way we use technology has completely transformed the way we live or lives.</p><p>(2)Educators, too, have seen firsthand the benefits of technology in the classroom. According to a study by IT Trade Association CompTIA just released this month, around 75 percent of educators think that technology has a positive impact on the education process. Educators also recognize the importance of developing these technological skills in students so they will be prepared to enter the workforce once they complete their schooling.</p><p>(3)The impact that technology has had on today’s schools has been quite significant. This widespread adoption of technology has completely changed how teachers teach and students learn. Teachers are learning how to teach with emerging technologies (tablets, iPads, Smart Boards, digital cameras, and computers), while students are using advanced technology to shape how they learn. By embracing and integrating technology in the classroom, we are setting our students up for a successful life outside of school.</p><p>(4)A few benefits of using technology are obvious. Technology in the classroom makes learning more fun. Technology not only prepares students for the future, but also improves retention rate. Besides, technology helps students learn at their own pace, and technology connects learning sources with students.</p><p>(5)As technology changes very fast, educators need to keep up with the times in order to best prepare our students for this ever-changing world that we live in. While we just saw how integrating technology into the classroom has its benefits, it is important to note that traditional learning processes are just as essential. Take time to learn about each element of ed-tech that you will incorporate into your classroom.</p><p><i>(Adapted from: http://www.teachhub.com/benefits-technology-classroom)</i></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>One of the negative effects of technology on the educators is that ….</p>', NULL, 'pilihan_ganda', '<p>Tipe soal ini adalah <i>Finding Detailed Information</i> yang bertujuan untuk mencari informasi terkait dampak negatif teknologi terhadap para pengajar di dalam teks.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Pada paragraf 5 dibahas mengenai kekurangan yang muncul bersamaan dengan sisi positif dari penggunaan teknologi dalam pendidikan saat ini. Dua kalimat berikut “<i>As technology changes very fast, educators need to keep up with the times… Take time to learn about each element of ed-tech that you will incorporate into your classroom.</i>” (Karena teknologi berubah sangat cepat, para pendidik perlu mengikuti perkembangan zaman…. Luangkan waktu untuk mempelajari setiap elemen dalam pendidikan berbasis teknologi yang akan kamu gunakan di dalam ruang kelasmu) menunjukkan bahwa para pengajar harus selalu belajar dan menyesuaikan diri dengan berbagai macam teknologi dan penemuan dalam pendidikan.</p><p>Opsi A (Para guru harus belajar lebih keras dibandingkan para murid mereka) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Pada paragraf tersebut tidak menunjukkan adanya pembahasan terkait usaha yang dibutuhkan para guru yang dibandingkan dengan para muridnya.</p><p>Opsi B (Mereka telah merubah kemampuan berpikir mereka dalam pembelajaran) <strong>tidak tepat.</strong>. Perubahan kemampuan berpikir tidak menjadi fokus utama dalam kekurangan dari penggunaan teknologi pada pendidikan.</p><p>Opsi C (Mereka harus tetap beradaptasi dengan penemuan atau teknologi terbaru) <strong>tepat</strong>. Pernyataan pada opsi ini sesuai untuk dapat dijadikan dari kekurangan atau dampak negatif dari kehadiran teknologi bagi pendidikan.</p><p>Opsi D (informasi menjadi cepat usang karena teknologi berubah dengan cepat) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Kualitas dari informasi tidak dibahas penuh pada paragraf 5, sehingga opsi ini tidak sesuai dengan konteks pembahasan.</p><p>Opsi E (Mereka tidak punya waktu untuk mempertahankan kemampuan dan kehidupan sosial mereka) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Kemampuan untuk kehidupan sosial dari para pendidik tidak dicerminkan pada dampak negatif dari kehadiran teknologi bagi pendidikan.</p><p><strong>Jadi, jawaban yang tepat adalah C.</strong></p>', NULL, 'Finding Detailed Information', '2025-06-30 03:35:08', '2025-06-30 03:35:08', NULL, 7, 35, 7, 'Diterima'),
(340, '<p><strong>(1)</strong> Television was once the newest technology in our homes, and then came videos and computers. Today’s children are growing up in a rapidly changing digital age that is far different from their parents. A variety of technologies are all around in our homes, offices, and schools. When used wisely, technology and media can support learning and relationships. Enjoyable and engaging shared experiences that optimize the potential for children’s learning and development can support children’s relationships both with adults and their peers.</p><p><strong>(2)</strong> Based on some evidence by research, there has never been more important time to apply principles of development and learning when considering the use of cutting-edge technologies and new media as the so-called interactive media. Interactive media refers to digital and analog materials, including software programs, applications (apps), some children’s television programming, e-books, the internet, and other forms of content designed to facilitate active and creative use by young children and to encourage social engagement with other children and adults.</p><p><strong>(3)</strong> When the integration of technology and interactive media in early childhood programs is built upon solid developmental foundations, and early childhood professionals are aware of both the challenges and the opportunities, educators are positioned to improve program quality by intentionally leveraging the potential of technology and media for the benefit of every child.</p><p><strong>(4)</strong> This statement provides guidance for early childhood educators about the use of technology and interactive media in ways that can optimize opportunities for young children’s development. In this statement, the definition of technology tools encompasses a broad range of digital devices such as computers, tablets, multi-touch screens, interactive whiteboards, mobile devices, cameras, audio recorders, electronic toys, games, e-book readers, and older analog devices still being used such as tape recorders, record and cassette players, projectors, and microscopes.</p><p><strong>(5)</strong> By appropriately and intentionally using the technology of his day - broadcast television - to connect with each individual child and with parents and families, it is demonstrated the positive potential of using technology and media in ways that are grounded in principles of child development.</p><p><i>(Adapted from: https://issuu.com/naeyc/docs/ps_technology_issuu_may2012)</i></p><p>How does the second sentence relate to the first sentence in paragraph 2? The second sentence</p>', NULL, 'pilihan_ganda', '<p>Tipe pertanyaan di atas berkaitan dengan <i>’Author’s Writing Organisation’</i> yang bertujuan untuk mencari hubungan antara kalimat pertama dan kedua pada paragraf 2.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Kalimat pertama membicarakan pentingnya memanfaatkan teknologi dan media baru untuk menerapkan prinsip-prinsip pengembangan dan pembelajaran.</p><p>Kalimat kedua mengatakan bahwa media interaktif dapat mendorong keterlibatan sosial anak-anak dan orang dewasa.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Kedua kalimat tersebut membahas media interaktif yang membawa manfaat bagi anak-anak. Hal tersebut terlihat dari penggalan berikut: <i>(1) … to facilitate active and creative use by young children</i> (... untuk memfasilitasi penggunaan aktif dan kreatif oleh anak-anak); <i>(2) and to encourage social engagement with other children and adults</i> (dan untuk mendorong keterlibatan sosial dengan anak-anak lain dan orang dewasa).</p><p>Walaupun ada satu penggalan yang menyebutkan manfaat media interaktif bagi orang dewasa, anak-anak merupakan target utama dalam bacaan di atas.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Oleh karena itu, dapat disimpulkan bahwa kalimat kedua menekankan pentingnya media interaktif bagi anak-anak.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Opsi A (menunjukkan pentingnya media interaktif bagi kehidupan anak-anak) <strong>tepat</strong>. Pernyataan pada opsi ini merepresentasikan adanya keuntungan dari media interaktif bagi anak-anak.</p><p>Opsi B (berpendapat bahwa media interaktif hanya mencakup materi digital) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Terdapat salah satu penggalan dari kalimat kedua yang berbunyi: <i>”Interactive media refers to <strong>digital and analog materials</strong>”</i>. Informasi tersebut menyatakan bahwa materi analog juga dapat digunakan sebagai media interaktif.</p><p>Opsi C (menjelaskan definisi dan contoh-contoh media interaktif) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Penulis tidak mendefinisikan media interaktif pada kalimat kedua. Penggalan <i>”Interactive media refers to digital and analog materials …”</i> (Media interaktif mengacu pada materi digital dan analog …) memperlihatkan jenis media yang dapat dimanfaatkan untuk melaksanakan pembelajaran interaktif.</p><p>Opsi D (menyatakan bahwa anak-anak dan orang dewasa familiar dengan teknologi digital) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Penulis tidak mencantumkan informasi terkait seberapa paham anak-anak dan orang dewasa zaman sekarang terhadap penggunaan teknologi digital.</p><p>Opsi E (menunjukkan bahwa media interaktif dapat mendukung hubungan sosial antara orang dewasa) <strong>tidak tepat</strong>. Kalimat kedua menjelaskan bahwa media interaktif dapat mendukung keterlibatan sosial antara orang dewasa dan anak-anak, bukan di antara orang dewasa saja.</p><p><strong>Maka, jawaban yang tepat adalah A.</strong></p>', NULL, 'Author\'s Attitude and Writing Organization', '2025-06-30 03:46:43', '2025-06-30 03:46:43', NULL, 7, 35, 7, 'Diterima');
